        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 16 at 9:00PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 859 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 19 miles east of Parker School, or 22 miles south of
Chinook, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cleveland and Lloyd.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
